SIMPLE: dewy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dewy
<hw>Dew"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining
to dew; resembling, consisting of, or moist with, dew.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>dewy</qex> mist⟦br⟧
Went and watered all the ground.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When <qex>dewy</qex> eve her curtain draws.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Falling gently and beneficently, like the
dew.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Dewy</qex> sleep ambrosial.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Resembling a dew-covered surface;
appearing as if covered with dew.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dexamethasone</ent>⟦br⟧
